# üêû bug report

### Description

If an angular project is build in production mode, invalid css may be generated if css-variables are used.

**Example**
If the following css file is compiled via `ng build --prod`, the border properties gets combined to `border: var(--borderThickness) solid #000`, that will be resolved to `border:  5px 10px 15px 20px solid #000` which is invalid css. As a result, no border is shown.

**CSS**
```
:host {
  --borderThickness: 5px 10px 15px 20px;
}

.b {
  border-width: var(--borderThickness);
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: black;

  /* Workaround */
  /*
    border: 0 solid black;
    border-width: var(--borderThickness);
  */
}

```

**HTML**
```
<div class="b">
  <p>My parent's border is only visible in debug mode. :(</p>
</div>

```
### Result

**Debug Mode**

![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1791936/111458503-c7be4600-8719-11eb-96c0-d70c659e8188.png)


